title: blinking cat script python
content:
import time
import sys
import pyfiglet
print("\n"*2)
bigtext = pyfiglet.figlet_format("Cat Blinking",font="slant")
print(bigtext)



def display_cat(closed=True):
    sys.stdout.write("\033[F\033[F\033[F\033[F")  # Move the cursor up 4 lines
    sys.stdout.write("\r /\_/\  \n") 
    if closed:
        sys.stdout.write("\r( -.- )  _\n")
    else:
        sys.stdout.write("\r( o.o )  _\n")
    sys.stdout.write("\r > ^ <  / *\n")
    sys.stdout.write("\r( _  _)/ \n")
    sys.stdout.flush()  # Force the output to update

# Run the blinking effect
print("\n" * 4)  # Create initial space for the cat to be printed
while True:
    display_cat(closed=True)   # Cat with eyes closed
    time.sleep(0.5)            # Pause for a bit
    display_cat(closed=False)  # Cat with eyes open
    time.sleep(0.5)            # Pause for a bit
